Definition: a religious movement by Persian Shiite Muslims in 17th century Iran that is opposed to the Akhbari
Example: Usuli Shiism produced the politically active caste of priests that is a distinctive feature of Iranian Shiism
Synonyms: religious_movement, noun, location, Iran, r, a, religious, movement, by, Persian, Shiite, Muslims, in, th, century, that, is, opposed, to, the, Akhbari, Shiism, produced, politically, active, caste, of, priests, distinctive, feature, Iranian
Category: noun.group
